claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table presenting vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages with 95% confidence intervals for different influenza vaccines—recombinant quadrivalent vaccine (RIV4), standard-dose egg-based quadrivalent vaccine (SD-IIV4), and RIV4 plus high-dose egg-based HD-IIV4 plus adjuvanted vaccine (Adj-IV)—compared to no vaccination, stratified by age group (18–64 years and ≥65 years) and subgroup (overall, males, females). The table reports VE data for various influenza vaccines but does not mention or link mutations arising during cell- or egg-based production to reduced effectiveness, so it does not support the claim. Note: No direct information on vaccine production methods or mutation occurrences is provided in the table; the image quality is sufficient to confirm absence of mutation data.
